data.title: Louisiana Ragin' Cajuns
data.meta_description: Nate Douglas (58) Defensive End - 2010 (Junior): Appeared in 11 games, starting four in a five-game stretch beginning with first career start vs. MT (Sept. 2...
data.text:
2010 (Junior): Appeared in 11 games, starting four in a five-game stretch beginning with first career start vs. MT (Sept. 25)...Did not start or play at Troy (shoulder injury)...Led all D-linemen in tackles...Posted a career-best seven tackles at FAU, adding 1.5 sacks and a forced fumble...Tallied two or three tackles in every other game...Notched a sack at Ohio.

2009 (Sophomore): Did not compete (not cleared medically for football activities).

2008 (Redshirt Freshman): Played 12 games as a reserve defensive end...Led all defensive lineman in tackles and tackles-for-loss...Ranked third in sacks...Blocked an extra point at FAU...Posted at least two tackles in 10 games...Posted a season-high five tackles vs. Kent State...Collected or shared a tackle-for loss in seven different games.

2007 (Freshman): Redshirted, did not play.

Milton: Honorable mention All-State selection among the Florida Class 6A ranks following the 2006 season...Was a member of the Pensacola New Journal's All-Area team and an All-District 1-4A pick after recording 100 tackles and seven sacks as a junior in 2005...Also played tight end.
